data.title: Find Out Where You Can Watch WOW: Women Of Wrestling Your Local Market
data.meta_description: Fans now know how they’ll be able to watch WOW – Women Of Wrestling. As previously announced, WOW – Women of Wrestling will return on September 17 with the premiere of new episodes that will air on networks affiliated with CBS.
data.text:
Fans now know how they’ll be able to watch WOW – Women Of Wrestling.

As previously announced, WOW – Women of Wrestling will return on September 17 with the premiere of new episodes that will air on networks affiliated with CBS.

According to PWInsider, the episodes will air on the following networks in a number of major markets:

New York City, NY – WLNY channel 55 at 11 PM Eastern

Los Angeles, CA – KCAL channel 9 at 2 AM Pacific

Chicago, IL – WCIU – CW26 at 12 PM Central

Philadelphia, PA – WPSG – CW 57 at 11 PM Eastern

Dallas/Fort Worth, TX – KTXA-TV at 1 AM Central

San Francisco, CA – CW affiliate KBCW 44 – 2:30 AM Pacific

Atlanta, GA – WUPA CW affiliate channel 69 – 12 AM Eastern

Houston, TX – KIAH – 12 AM Central

Washington, DC – WDCW channel 50 – 2 PM Eastern

Boston, MA – WSBK MyNetworkTV38 – 12 AM Eastern

Additional confirmed timeslots include :

Richmond, VA – CW Richmond Channel 65 – 10 PM Eastern

Charlotte, NC – WCCB Charlotte CW at 7 PM and 11 PM Eastern

Cincinnati, OH – WSTR 64 – 12 AM Eastern

Minneapolis, MN – CW channel 23 – 1 PM Central

WOW previously signed a multi-year deal with ViacomCBS in October 21.

WrestleZone will provide more information as it becomes available.
